    "SpaceClaim / Ansys Discovery"
  ],
  "formatRelationships": {
    "category": "CAD",
    "extensions": [".sat", ".sab"],
    "relatedFormats": ["STEP", "BREP", "X_T", "X_B", "CATPART"],
    "note": "SAT is the ASCII form of ACIS kernel geometry; SAB is the binary equivalent (same structure, faster to read). Parasolid uses X_T/X_B as analogues. STEP and IGES are neutral formats that export BREP geometry similar to SAT. Open CASCADE natively reads BREP; SAT requires the ACIS kernel or a licensed reader."
  },
